76561198026705042,Recommended,237850,31538687,Posted: 4 May,all,𝓝𝓪𝓪𝓻𝓲𝓼,"Dreamfall Chaptershttp://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=917712626At the moment of this review I have played for 24 hours. I could go for another round to see a different situation.Do I think this game is good and can I recommend it?YES.Almost 1600 hands up vs 30.A few words about this game? It's... a Journey!! and I love Crow, and Enu, and Likho.Do you have to play the previous games to enjoy this one? No, but it would be better. This is the ending of a trilogy, if you ever have read a trilogy you will understand.http://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=914667693Graphics:The game uses the UNITY graphic engine. Well... it has it's limitations, do not expect awesome animations or movements, but in general it aproves. You will swich between Arcadia and Stark, and each one of them are really well recreated (magic world and Science world) As I always say, a picture really does paint a thousand words so... take a look into some screenshots or gameplay videos you can find around.Music:I love it. Obviously it not the symphonic orchestra but the music really fets with each one of the most important events that you will live playing the game. The ambience is also really acomplished but you will find sometimes that you have heard that soundtrack a lot of times but well... the game is really long in time...http://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=917503996Story:Once upon a time....  two worlds, the world of science and the world of magic. Stark and Arcadia. Both worlds were unaware of the existence of the other, except for some exceptional persons who could switch between them or dream themself into the other world. And surrounding all of it, the Balance, because when there is light there is darkness, when there is magic there is science, when there is life there is death.But that balance is breaking, the magic is being under attack on Arcadia and somehow Stark is being affected too.You are Zöe, you are a Dreamer and you saved Stark from a conspiration to steal dreams from the people with a dreamachine and use it to mass control the population, but you went into a coma. Now is time to wake up.This is the last of three games that are linked and although they can appear old... well, I recommend you to play them.For real, this is the BEST part of the game and the ending is really... an ENDING.Gameplay:It's a point and click game. Well yes, you can use a gamepad and you will walk and run with keys but the essence is that, a point and click game with 3rd person view. With puzzles to be resolved that usually are easy and the different parts of it can be found in the same area. But, the strong point of this game is that almost all your decisions will affect the game. It sounds like a ""telltale"" game, like the walking dead. No... the end is not 100% writen and no matter what you do, that won't change. Here you can save one life instead of another for real, if you help one person in chapter 2, that person will be alive and will affect your future. If you killed that person, that will change your present.Negative point:Well, I have think hard about this... I find no negative point. Well, I would change somethings like the Unity engine, more npcs walking around... but it's not important, so... let's say I really really like this game like it is and I have really loved playing it."
