76561197967099822,Recommended,237850,28318680,"Posted: 11 December, 2016",all,Zdavem,"This is one of those bizarre examples where I am at a loss when I comes to explain what is so great about it from a purely gameplay related perspective. Because in that regard it doesn’t really do anything special, and the tried and tested stuff it does do in terms of mechanics is not especially well-made. Beautiful graphics with some very awkward animations. It’s essentially is an old-style point and click game trapped inside a third person choose-your-own-adventure-novel. So nothing new and/or exiting there.But it is in terms of story, characters and worldbuilding it excels beyond most things I have ever played. The actual narrative was a bit jarring at first; playing as two different characters in two completely different worlds, but once some familiarity sets in the rest of the ride is amazing. I don’t want to get in to too much detail but this is one of those rare examples where the ever-rising stakes scenario actually feels earned.All in all, an amazing experience. Top marks.(I played most of the game offline. The real time spent playing should be round 30-35 hours)"
