76561198000030523,Recommended,237850,33814747,Posted: 26 July,all,Calyxie,"After just finishing this game i must say my emotions are high... Now before saying more, I haven't played the first games of Dreamfall Chapters.I have read some rewiews for this game and if you are a returning fan I wouldn't be able to give you answers on does this game continues well or bad from the first ones.Or if you are a new to this game and haven't played the first ones, I cannot again tell if this game is better then the last ones or if playing the first ones is neccesary here (many people have said that playing the first games will answer some questions that are unanswered in this game, but honestly I didn't feel much of need to... I mean there were some parts yes, but we will get to that).Now this game is purely a story telling stand of point. Yes you are able to move around in a 3D world, but there is no fighting, or timely combat. Just pure story and it is done superbly. Oh and decision making... Lots and lots of decision making and uh some puzzles. Yes these too.Since the game is so much about dialoge and listening to the characters you play as, it is really important that the voice acting is good. One thing i always look for in games over breathtaking graphics or never before heard game mechanics are interesting characters (someone you can feel connected to when playing, something to take you into a jorney and make you feel part of it not just slide through the events of the game unconnected, leaving you feel empty). Interesting characters make (me atleast) players just so much more interested in the story. And well the voice acting in this game is superb. This game makes you think about your decisions that you make and hard, because well... you do not want to end up dead in the next chapter, but always making the best decision for yourself, isn't the best one for the cause. So yes there are decisions. Loooots of em.Now the characters. There were characters that i immideatly fell in love with, for their character, funny and well thought out voice lines. It all fit. The rest of the characters were just pefect fit for their role. You weren't suppose to laugh when they said something, but they made the story good and inderesting.Many have compared the choise makings in this game to Life is Strange. I do not honestly agree with most of these. In Life is Strange to be honest no other choises mattered besides the last one. Your ""friend"" or the ""town"". Dreamfall Chapters goes way deeper in that. There were choises that came to haunt me in book five that i had made in book 2. I feel like i have to play through this game again just to see what choises i could have made differently, what could i have done better, or what did i miss by being an idiot and not seeing an obvious choise i was supposed to make.And yes the game story. This is my second reason why i loved this game so much. Characters and story. Again. Not playing the first game might give me a half understanding or feeling of the events of this game, but honestly i do not care not right now. The story is great. If you are a fan of futuristic, modern world full of technology and then also love the world of magic, non magicals and the world in which they live in, this game is like 2 fists in both of your eyeballs.As much as i would love to just praise the story to the heavens i really cannot. There were parts where i was sitting on the edge of my seat, holding my breath in, waiting to see what would happen now or bite my fingernails off worrying over some of my decisions.... There was also parts that felt really dragging on and really not well thought through in my oppinion or even neccesary. The game delivers the story well and the end was truly breathtaking with an unexpected twist at the very end, but it is not perfect. Still it makes together for an awesome story... still.So i'd say this game is very much worth for a anyone who enjoys point and click game with awesome story and stunning graphics.So really short: Point and click game, awesome story, great and awesome characters, really cool enviorment in both Zoe and Kians worlds, puzzles, and well the decisions.... many many decisions in this game.Feel like home with that, I think you would enjoy Dreamfall Chapters. Yeah...If you still want advice. Well i would really reccomend this game. It was very interesting and really really enjoyable."
