76561198029390870,Recommended,237850,26369223,"Posted: 2 November, 2016",all,Spazzies,"This one is by far my favorite installment in the series (And I'm not even finished with it as of now but going by other reviews I've read I don't think my opinion is likely to change).Not to say that it doesn't have a few rather nasty flaws. For starters they could have toned down the political aspects a notch or two, especially during the first couple of hours you spend running around Stark. It quickly got to the point for me to where I was just rolling my eyes and wanting to rush through the campaign errands. It doesn't help that I'm playing the game during one of the most ridiculous election cycles in US history. When I turn the tv off and opt for some gaming instead, the last thing I want to be faced with is more political bs. So that aspect was rather disappointing to me and I view it as being inconsiderate on the writer's part to be imposing very strong views of a touchy subject onto their players. The other thing I found a bit annoying was how they didn't improve the speed at which you ""jog"" and yet there are enough back and forth ""quests"" that you'll be yearning for a rocket propelled jet pack after the first hour. Typical filler. Make it take 10 minutes to get from point A to point B and call it gameplay.Now for the positives. The thing I love most about this game is the atmosphere. In my opinion it does an even better job of combining spirituality and magic with science and technology. With many games that attempt this, it's often too abstract and weird but here I find it enthralling. I liked that many of the characters found in the first two are still around and in some cases, more interesting. Nearly everything is choice driven and your choices do impact even minor details, which makes for better enjoyment of multiple play-throughs. The voice acting is fantastic, the soundtrack is beautiful, the graphics much improved and the story is mysteriously interesting. All in all it's a great adventure for the price."
