,Recommended,237850,23697669,"Posted: 21 June, 2016",all,Michelle Obama,"Here's the bottom-line: if you've played The Longest Journey and its sequel, Dreamfall: The Longest Journey, then you had might as well play this and see how it all ends. Also, Crow is back and he's as delightful as ever.Book 5 is released and it ties up virtually all the loose ends from a story roughly 17 years in the making. The ending is satisfying. If you're like me, and grew up playing The Longest Journey, then you gotta play this game to see how it all ends. No need to read further; hop to it (or wait until the game is on sale).Anyway, the game isn't great. But it has great moments. The earlier episodes are repetitive and a slog. Still, they lay the groundwork for some fantastic set pieces and epic moments in Episodes 4 and 5.A lot of your choices end up being non-choices; no real impact on the ending. Still, they add a lot of flavor, and they do a good job of making you pay attention to details of whether something is a good idea to pursue or not.The animation and environments of the game leave a lot to be desired. The characters move clunkily, unbelievably.  And the environments, while cool at first, are boring after you've ran through the same areas over and over for four episodes on various errands. Finally, though, episodes 4 and 5 introduce some new environments that are gorgeous to look at, and, thankfully, they don't overstay their welcome.As an adventure game, Dreamfall: Chapters is consistently underwhelming and simple-minded. No, I don't miss the obtuse puzzles of TLJ, but I wish there was some more depth to the gameplay. I can't help but feel like the episodic nature of the game only hurt it in the end; but I suppose there was no other way of financing this project.But let's be real: you're not going to play it because you're expecting an adventure game with memorable puzzles that make you feel like a genius.You're going to play it because Ragnar Tornquist created a captivating world populated by relatable characters that you care about.And you're going to enjoy it."
