,Recommended,237850,23672394,"Posted: 20 June, 2016",all,Lint Wizard,"(Episode Five is the primary focus of this spoiler-free review)It's the best possible ending to the Longest Journey series. The previous entry, Dreamfall, was utterly ruthless in its emotional brutality - a tragedy compounded by time, akin to if Empire Strikes Back had gone without a planned sequel for over a decade. Dreamfall Chapters is the complete opposite: it doesn't merely crank out the happy ending that fans clamored for; it presents a thorough, multithreaded series of conclusions that expertly merge Dreamfall's dark maturity with the first game's sense of wonder and magic. The former is certainly the dominant element, though, make no mistake, but it's used to satisfying effect.Also, those jerks made me burst into tears within 5 or 10 minutes of starting the fifth episode. A day later and it still makes me misty-eyed. If it hadn't been for the achievement text that popped up I think I would have literally died of sadness and missed all the bittersweet or even happy conclusions."
