,Recommended,237850,24099797,"Posted: 4 July, 2016",all,tuncstic,"While I loved playing both Longest Journey and Dreamfall, I REALLY hated the ending of both. For that reason, I was hesitant to buy Dreamfall Chapters. The reviewers liked the ending though, so in the end I bought it. Having now played it to completion, I agree that this is a good ending to the series. It's too bad there wasn't enough money to do the sequel.My main criticism of the game is that, even with rather modest graphics, it requires a substantial GPU to get a decent frame rate - at 1280x720 and Medium quality, I only got 15 FPS with my GTX 720.Other downsides:- It is not possible to move the cursor independently from the camera. This makes for a somewhat dizzying experience, and also makes it hard to look for objects to interact with, especially at low frame rates.- No visible cursor, and objects you can interact with are not highlighted until they are centered in the view - see previous point.- Some puzzles are quite difficult, and you can't advance in the story until you solve them. I had to resort to a walkthough for several. In most cases. the difficulty is quite artificial - it does not enhance the story.- Voices for background conversations often drowned out the main conversation. This may have been fixed in later patch levels.My rating: 7/10"
