,Recommended,237850,16563981,"Posted: 20 June, 2015",all,DCDarkling,"What is Dreamfall ChaptersIt is a successor to a series I never played, but the previous games are on steam for the interested people.""Dreamfall Chapters"" is a game which heavily features lore & choice rather then (fps) action.You do not get to fight or sprint around like mad.Instead you walk/run around, talking a lot to people, looking at the world & try to solve puzzles as 'a normal person' would. Conversation choices & actions featureheavilyin this.Lore & discussionsThe game in essence tells a story and you get to make various choices during the game on how it progresses. These can be small or big choices like lying to someone, or reacting to situations in certain ways.If you like lore, choices and a lot of ingame discussions this is the game for you. If you like mindless action, you might as well stop reading here.Another big point is simply this.. female protagonist.Most games either have a male protagonist or, incase of a female one, sexualise her.As roughly half the gamers out there are female, its nice to see more games which also include a female protagonist.Note that NOT all chapters of the game are released YET. (again, indie company.)While some question this choice it means they already get a income in sales on the chapters which are released, to keep making the new chapters.This makes sure the chapters we already have are NOT RUSHED.Not rushing a game release is rare in these days.Graphics & looksWhile not, per se, up to par with triple A games, the graphics do look rather stunning. The occasional glitch can occur, but ive seen those in games of any 'quality'.Considering even that this game is made by a small indie developer who even had to kickstart it, I would say we very much get more than expected.The game has its own style, which works well for the story in question.The main 2 characters tend to change looks and clothes depending on situation (and chapter), further adding to some realism.I personally did not experience any fps issues. (but of course your mileage may vary)ACTUALLY with further testing it seems on my i7 970 + GTX 770, my fps on the 'awesome' setting is averaging around 30-45. I just do not notice due to gsync)SoundThe game has good music, nice voiceacting and plenty of ambient sounds to make you feel at home, or better said in the world.It is at times however hard to hear voice from music and ambient. Some tweaking in your settings may help against this.I left subtitles on to make sure I did not miss any words in sentences, as the default config can make that happen. Other noises then the voices talking can drown out the convo at times.So some minor tweaks needed on what is otherwise good music and sound. (on a 2.0 speaker & headset setup. I did not test more speakers)ControlsControls are fine and work well for the game IF you account for one big thing.For MANY functions its NOT HOLD KEY but CLICK KEY. There, if you are used to games where you hold keys I just saved you a headache.While functions like movement and running require you to HOLD they key, function like using and opening the RADIAL MENU requires you to CLICK and not hold.If you hold the (mouse)key the radial menu will open and do... nothing. You are supposed to click it open and then click on the option you want to perform.This method of control is absolutely no problem in playing the game as long as you know that its click.Conclusion & TLDRThe game is heavily based on lore, discussions and choice. If this is your thing YAY, if not, NAY.Graphic-wise great game, especially considering its from a indie company. Great however is not perfect. (Is any game ever)Nice music & voiceacting & ambience. But the volume mixture between voices & other sounds needs to be manually adjusted.If you hold the radial menu rather then click it, you are gona have a hard day. Click for the menu's.Female protagonist.Game is released in chapters and not all chapters are YET released. This increases budget for them to keep working on chapters while NOT rushing them. (aka we will not get junk.)"
