,Recommended,237850,12982729,"Posted: 17 November, 2014",all,~Sliggy Diggy~,"Having played and very much enjoyed the two prequels, I knew what I was hoping for but wasn't sure what to expect with this one, however I'm happy to say that I was not disappointed, in fact I was pleasantly surprised by how true it stayed to the others. Much like its predecessors, Chapters is dialogue and plot heavy, focusing on building a unique, believable fantasy atmosphere that really immerses you in its universe and characters. In addition, certain parts of the game were surprisingly open, allowing you to explore at your leisure should you so choose. It also appears to implement something new, different choices that the player can make when prompted which will have consequences later on as the game progresses, which remains to be seen. I only discovered one glitch, a couple of small, hard to find spots in a level that I clipped through completely by accident, and was afterwards able to run around in regions of the level where you're definitely not meant to be. The graphics are nothing short of amazing and subsequently might require a bit of a beefy computer to handle, and luckily I was able to get the full benefit of them with smooth performance. While the previous games will definitely help explain a lot of the events in this one, much of it is explained in this game alone, but I definitely recommend the trilogy as a whole."
