76561198003932649,Recommended,237850,25523374,"Posted: 16 September, 2016",all,Trillian,"I recommend Dreamfall Chapters, but to get the full experience, the player should seek out the first two games that this one has followed: 'The Longest Journey' (1) and 'Dreamfall: The Longest Journey' (2). The experience won't be as rich without them.Setting and artwork are glorious, though character movement and visuals are not a match for other games. However, the plot and storyline depth are so complex that player immersion is complete. All characters have their quirks and motivations - even the minor ones. Voice acting is impeccable. Every character is a hero of their own story, and we get to control two of them: Zoe and Kian, two characters from two worlds working towards a common goal.Some of the side missions feel a little bit like filler, but I personally didn't mind. There are multiple ways to solve a problem and different solutions attract different outcomes and reactions. The choices within are immense, and even though the storyline is forced, the paths taken to get there are so different that this game can be played again.There aren't many games out there like this, which is a shame."
