76561197982434623,Recommended,237850,30974658,Posted: 6 April,all,#SWAGASAURUS_WRECKS,"As someone who just finished this game, I'm writing this review for you as much as I am for me:TL;DR:Most spectacular adventure game you will play. Don't start on Chapters. The Longest Journey => Dreamfall:TLJ => Dreamfall Chapters.Pros:Epic adventure story, sci fi AND fantasy setting, music, voice acting, and visualsCons:Empty large environments (fixed in later chapters).Choppy AnimationsSome don't think the choices affect the game enough.For some of us, this was the longest journey. As a boy, my first adventure game was The Longest Journey and although I didn't understand all of it, it left me mystified. In 2006, Dreamfall: The Longest Journey cast my world asunder my childhood memories of April Ryan's incredible adventures were left on the ultimate cliffhanger and then there was the longest wait. Dreamfall Chapters and 2016 concluded this long painstaking wait and what a build up...Let me tell you, if you start from the beginning, you will be rewarded. This story does not disappoint in any form. It flawlessly combines science fiction and fantasy into a truly unique setting. Stark. Arcadia..If you are picking up this game and expecting a TellTale Games Walking Dead choices, this game was written with an ending in mind. It's been building towards finally connecting all the peices. You can make choices and they are going to make you cringe or worry or your characters might have regrets later in the game, but you're not going to alter the entire game.At times, the visuals are breath-taking. Although, when Red Thread Games started, I believed they were too beautiful. I would have prefered the point and click format of The Longest Journey with more things to interact with. Sometimes the areas are confusing the navigate and there are only a few things to interact with. You're supposed to only go one place but you can travel the whole length of the area with little to do. It is annoying and wastes your time. But this problem resolved in the later episodes.The animations are also stiff and choppy at times. However they accomplish the job of telling the story which is really all this game is about. I didn't mind using my imagination though. Fortunately, the voice acting really makes up for anything lost in the animation.The music is amazing and gives me shivers every time I load up the game.Right next to Life is Strange, this is my favorite interactive movie I have ever watched. It breaks your heart and swaddles it next to a cozy fire, simultanously.  I will never forget you April, Zoe, Kian, Saga, and Crow. Crow, thank you Red Thread Games for the best side kick that ever existed. I don't know how you pulled off such a satisfying ending. The wait was worth it. Every second."
